      • generateOrKeyRecoverTokenAsByteArray

        byte[] generateOrKeyRecoverTokenAsByteArray​(AuthenticationToken authenticationToken,
                                            String username,
                                            String password,
                                            String hardTokenSN,
                                            String keySpecification,
                                            String keyAlgorithm)
                                     throws CADoesntExistsException,
                                            AuthorizationDeniedException,
                                            NotFoundException,
                                            EjbcaException
        Creates a server-generated keystore. The method must be preceded by a editUser call, either to set the userstatus to 'new' or to add non-existing users and the user's token must be set to org.ejbca.core.protocol.ws.client.gen.UserDataVOWS.TOKEN_TYPE_P12.
        Authorization requirements: 
         - /administrator
 - /ca/<ca of user>
 - /ca_functionality/create_certificate
 - /endentityprofilesrules/<end entity profile>/view_end_entity
 - /ra_functionality/view_end_entity
        Additional authorization requirements for (non key recovery) clearing of password: 
         - /endentityprofilesrules/<end entity profile>/edit_end_entity
 - /ra_functionality/edit_end_entity
        Additional authorization requirements for key recovery: 
         - /endentityprofilesrules/<end entity profile>/keyrecovery
 - /ra_functionality/keyrecovery
        Parameters:
        authenticationToken - administrator performing the action.
        username - the unique username.
        password - the password sent with editUser call.
        hardTokenSN - If the certificate should be connected with a hard token, it is possible to map it by give the hardTokenSN here, this will simplify revocation of a tokens certificates. Use null if no hardtokenSN should be associated with the certificate.
        keySpecification - that the generated key should have, examples are 2048 for RSA or secp256r1 for ECDSA.
        keyAlgorithm - that the generated key should have, RSA, ECDSA. Use one of the constants in AlgorithmConstants.KEYALGORITHM_...
        Returns:
        the generated or reused key store as byte array.
        Throws:
        CADoesntExistsException - if a referenced CA does not exist.
        AuthorizationDeniedException - if client isn't authorized to request.
        NotFoundException - if the user could not be found.
        EjbcaException - any EjbcaException.

                            throws AuthorizationDeniedException,
                                   KeyStoreException,
                                   InvalidAlgorithmParameterException,
                                   CADoesntExistsException,
                                   IllegalKeyException,
                                   CertificateCreateException,
                                   IllegalNameException,
                                   CertificateRevokeException,
                                   CertificateSerialNumberException,
                                   CryptoTokenOfflineException,
                                   IllegalValidityException,
                                   CAOfflineException,
                                   InvalidAlgorithmException,
                                   CustomCertificateSerialNumberException,
                                   AuthStatusException,
                                   AuthLoginException,
                                   EndEntityProfileValidationException,
                                   NoSuchEndEntityException,
                                   CertificateSignatureException,
                                   CertificateEncodingException,
                                   CertificateException,
                                   NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                                   InvalidKeySpecException
        This method generates a new pkcs12 or jks token for a user, and key recovers the token, if the user is configured for that in EJBCA.
        Parameters:
        administrator - administrator performing the action.
        username - username in ejbca
        password - password for user
        caid - caid of the CA the user is registered for
        keyspec - name of ECDSA key or length of RSA and DSA keys (endEntityInformation.extendedInformation.keyStoreAlgorithmSubType has priority over this value)
        keyalg - AlgorithmConstants.KEYALGORITHM_RSA, AlgorithmConstants.KEYALGORITHM_DSA or AlgorithmConstants.KEYALGORITHM_ECDSA (endEntityInformation.extendedInformation.keyStoreAlgorithmType has priority over this value)
        notBefore - The date at which the private key starts to be valid, or null
        notAfter - The date at which the private key should be considered expired, or null
        createJKS - true to create a JKS, false to create a PKCS12
        loadkeys - true if keys should be recovered
        savekeys - true if generated keys should be stored for keyrecovery
        reusecertificate - true if the old certificate should be reused for a recovered key
        endEntityProfileId - the end entity profile the user is registered for
        Returns:
        a keystore
        Throws:
        AuthorizationDeniedException - if the authentication token was not allowed access to the EEP or CA of the end entity, to recover keys, to issue certificates
        KeyStoreException - if keys were set to be recovered, but no key recovery data was found
        InvalidAlgorithmParameterException - if the given parameters (keyspec, keyalg) are inappropriate for this key pair generator.
        CADoesntExistsException - if the CA defined by caid does not exist
        AuthLoginException - If the password was incorrect.
        AuthStatusException - If the end entity's status is incorrect.
        CustomCertificateSerialNumberException - (no rollback) if custom serial number is registered for user, but it is not allowed to be used (either missing unique index in database, or certificate profile does not allow it
        InvalidAlgorithmException - if the signing algorithm in the certificate profile (or the CA Token if not found) was invalid.
        CAOfflineException - if the CA was offline
        IllegalValidityException - if the validity defined by notBefore and notAfter was invalid
        CryptoTokenOfflineException - if the crypto token for the CA wasn't found
        CertificateSerialNumberException - if certificate with same subject DN or key already exists for a user, if these limitations are enabled in CA.
        CertificateRevokeException - (rollback) if certificate was meant to be issued revoked, but could not.
        IllegalNameException - if the certificate request contained an illegal name
        CertificateCreateException - (rollback) if certificate couldn't be created.
        IllegalKeyException - if the public key didn't conform to the constrains of the CA's certificate profile.
        NoSuchEndEntityException - if the end entity was not found
        EndEntityProfileValidationException - if the password doesn't fulfill the demands set by the EE profile
        CertificateSignatureException - if verification of the CA certificate failed
        InvalidKeySpecException - if the key specification defined in keys couldn't be found
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - if the algorithm defined in the keys couldn't be found
        CertificateException - if there was a problem with the certificate
        CertificateEncodingException - if there was a problem with the certificate
